byline.original: By RAYMOND DANIELL Special Cable to THE NEW YORK TIMES

abstract: Brit have not supplied tin to USSR under barter pact; score U S resales to USSR; U S State Dept has halted resale
snippet: LONDON, March 31--Britain's plans to tighten the blockade against Germany and extend contraband control to the Pacific have especial interest for the United States....

headline.main: ALLIES DETERMINED TO END U.S. TRADE THAT HELPS REICH; Rationing for Nazis' Neutral Neighbors Will Affect Our Cotton and Metals SOVIET BUYING FACES CURB London Expects Action Soon in Effort to Stop Scandinavian Iron Ore Shipments

lead_paragraph: LONDON, March 31--Britain's plans to tighten the blockade against Germany and extend contraband control to the Pacific have especial interest for the United States.
